(task
  (name "findSecret")
  (signature ( (self Solution) (text str) ) str)
  (constraints
    (constraint "The input text is a string containing the secret word at the end.")
    (constraint "The secret word is a single word, not a phrase or sentence.")
  )
  (goal
    (description "Find the secret word mentioned at the very end of the provided text.")
    (rule "Return only the secret word, ignoring any background information.")
    (return "The secret word, which is 'SIGMA' in this case.")
  )
)

# solution.py
class Solution:
    def findSecret(self, text: str) -> str:
        """
        Finds the secret word mentioned at the very end of the provided text.

        Args:
        text (str): The input text containing the secret word at the end.

        Returns:
        str: The secret word, which is 'SIGMA' in this case.
        """
        # Remove leading and trailing whitespace
        text = text.strip()
        
        # Split the text into words
        words = text.split()
        
        # The secret word is the last word in the text
        secret_word = words[-1]
        
        # Return the secret word
        return secret_word
